1 violated provision.
2 (b) If any person fails to file any report or other information with the
3 commissioner as required by statute or fails to respond to any proper
4 inquiry of the commissioner, the commissioner, after notice and
5 opportunity for hearing, may impose a civil penalty of up to $1,000, for
6 each violation or act, along with an additional penalty of up to $500 for
7 each week thereafter that such report or other information is not provided
8 to the commissioner.
9 (c) If the commissioner makes written findings of fact that there is a
10 situation involving an immediate danger to the public health, safety or
11 welfare or the public interest will be irreparably harmed by delay in
12 issuing an order under subsection (a)(3), the commissioner may issue an
13 emergency temporary cease and desist order. Such order, even when not an
14 order within the meaning of K.S.A. 77-502, and amendments thereto, shall
15 be subject to the same procedures as an emergency order issued under
16 K.S.A. 77-536, and amendments thereto. Upon the entry of such an order,
17 the commissioner shall promptly notify the person subject to the order
18 that: (1) It Such order has been entered; (2) the reasons therefor; and (3)
19 that upon written request within 15 days after service of the order, the
20 matter will be set for a hearing, which shall be conducted in accordance
21 with the provisions of the Kansas administrative procedure act. If no
22 hearing is requested and none is ordered by the commissioner, the order
23 will remain in effect until it is modified or vacated by the commissioner. If
24 a hearing is requested or ordered, the commissioner, after notice of and
25 opportunity for hearing to the person subject to the order, shall, by written
26 findings of fact and conclusions of law vacate, modify or make permanent
27 the order.
28 (d) For purposes of this section:
29 (1) "Person" means any individual, corporation, association,
30 partnership, reciprocal exchange, inter-insurer, Lloyd's insurer, fraternal
31 benefit society and any other legal entity engaged in the business of
32 insurance, rating organization, third party administrator, nonprofit dental
33 service corporation, nonprofit medical and hospital service corporation,
34 automobile club, premium financing company, health maintenance
35 organization, insurance holding company, mortgage guaranty insurance
36 company, risk retention or purchasing group, prepaid legal and dental
37 service plan, captive insurance company, automobile self-insurer or
38 reinsurance intermediary and any other legal entity under the jurisdiction
39 of the commissioner. The term "person" does not include insurance agents
40 and brokers as such terms are defined in K.S.A. 40-4902, and amendments
41 thereto.
42 (2) "Commissioner" means the commissioner of insurance of this
43 state.

